  // place queens row by row (one queen per row is guaranteed by construction)
  // track occupied columns and both diagonals with sets for O(1) conflict checks
  //   - a cell (row, col) lies on diagonal (row - col) and anti-diagonal (row + col)
  // backtrack: try each column in the current row, skip if column/diagonal is taken,
  // recurse to the next row, then undo the placement
