  // indices are in decreasing order front-to-back - the front is always
  // the index of the current window's maximum
  // for each new index i:
  //   1. pop from the back while nums[back] < nums[i] (they can never be
  //      the max again as long as nums[i] is still in the window)
  //   2. push i to the back
  //   3. pop from the front if it has fallen outside the window (i - k)
  //   4. once the window is full (i >= k - 1), record nums[front] as the max
